
> Remote Repository -
-- A remote repository is a version of your project hosted on the internet. 
   GitHub is a popular platform for hosting remote repositories, enabling you to collaborate with others and back up your code.

> Pull -
-- a> Pull from remote -> we want to update our local repository with the changes from GitHub.
      [Any time we start working on a project, we should get the most recent changes to our local copy.
       With Git, we can do that with pull. ]
-- b> pull is a combination of 2 different commands:
      fetch
      merge



